{"key":"processedPost-10427992","value":{"id":10427992,"first":10427947,"last":10435113,"when":1243751997,"utime":"05/31/09 09:39 AM","content":"If the grains are coming out too dry, you're probably failing to reduce the stove setting once pressure is reached.&nbsp; Every time the weight rattles, moisture is lost from your jars.&nbsp; I usually reduce heat so the PC runs at 14 psi, and the weight doesn't rattle at all.&nbsp; Make sure you're letting it vent steam with the weight off for several minutes at the start of each cycle before building pressure.<br />RR","title":"Re: how to stop from getting overcooked wbs?","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}